[DhtmlXQ_comment0]eg xqsycj tjm 039 1h1tp hw 1a2e||When the pawn is at the throat rank, it would not be able to capture red's bottom ranked pawn and a draw would normally ensue. The term for this is "太公坐椅".||Jim: More explanation to this endgame is given by GM Liu DianZhong. Please go to his lectures on endgames to eg board 020a.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment4]Correct move. This would allow black's elephant on the 7th file to protect the central file.[/DhtmlXQ_comment4]
[DhtmlXQ_comment12]Draw.[/DhtmlXQ_comment12]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1_11]And the elephant is caught after red plays H5+7 on the next move.||Jim: for beginners, I have added the moves so that you can see more clearly.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1_11]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1_15]And it is a sure win endgame for red now![/DhtmlXQ_comment1_15]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2_13]The black king is a sitting duck, and all that red has to do is to maneuver the horse for the final check, without moving to the central file that is.[/DhtmlXQ_comment2_13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment3_7]And all of the black pieces are pinned.||Black would have to play K4+1 to resolve this check. And red would simply play K5+1 or K5-1 and black would surely lose material.[/DhtmlXQ_comment3_7]
